history.content:
Hi there- just to make sure I understand your question...are you asking about UD CS classes? Or UD non-CS classes for the CS major? 

All UD CS classes are technical, and all are 4 units (with the exception of research units, which cannot be taken for a grade). Let me know if I misunderstood-

children.subject:
Hmm yeah, I was looking for UD CS department classes, similar to 370/375/195 which are upper divs but can't be taken for a grade.

Ah well :/

To answer the last question, do you have any personal recommendations?

history.content:
Hey, 

Just wanted to check if there were any non-technical upper div classes in CS that could be taken for a grade? This is basically in case I don't get off a Phase 2 waitlist this Fall :/ 

What about 2 or 3 unit upper div CS classes? 

Finally, as a CS minor who will probably be going into Public Health/Epidemiology/Biostats, what 3 classes would you personally recommend as most useful? 

For me, I'm leaning toward 3 of: 160, 186, 188 (taking this summer), 189, and 162 (in my own order of priority).
